xtension period is likewise payable in advance at the start of the extension period.\n\n7.2 Subscriptions can only be acquired in the form of in-app purchases. Billing is effected by the operator of the respective app store that collects payment on our behalf and undertakes reimbursement in cases such as cancellation as described in Section 13 of these T&amp;Cs. Payment is effected using the payment methods accepted by the app store operator.\n\n7.3 All prices include statutory value added tax.\n\n7.4 In the case of delay in payment, we reserve the right to impose default interest and may claim for further damages arising from the arrears.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n8. Ownership of rights and limitations of use\n\n8.1 We are the exclusive holder of the rights to all elements of the Ykings app including databases and accompanying computer programs, interface designs and specifi-cally the rights to use and ancillary copyrights on all content and on the know-how represented in, and forming the basis of, the app. The collection of content items as such on our websites may where applicable be protected as a database or data-base work within the meaning of Section 4 subsection 2 and Section 87 subsection 1 of the German Copyright Act (UrhG).\n\n8.2 Trademarks, company logos or other marks or intellectual property notices, copyright notices or serial numbers may not be removed or changed. This also applies to no-tices and marks of all kinds on printed copies of contents or from files exported from our websites.\n\n8.3 You receive an ordinary (non-exclusive), non-transferable and non-sublicenseable right limited to the term of the contract, which allows you to use the products, services and contents which are the subject of the contract for your own personal, private and non-commercial use exclusively.\n\n8.4 Direct or indirect transfer of the products, services and contents which are the subject of the contract to third parties or provision of access by third parties to said products, services and contents are not permitted.\n\n8.5 Unless further use is expressly permitted in these T&amp;Cs or on our website or is enabled by a corresponding function (e.g. download button), you are prohibited from edit-ing, changing, translating, presenting or demonstrating, publishing, exhibiting, repro-ducing or distributing the available content in whole or in part.\n\n8.6 You are only permitted to download or print out content where a download or print option is provided as a function (e.g. download button). You receive an ordinary (non-exclusive), non-transferable right to the use of the content which you have duly downloaded or printed out for your own non-commercial purposes for the duration of the contract.\n\n8.7 Use of content and data or database elements or the accessed data which extends beyond the use described above, specifically\n\n• copying of data, files, database elements or documents onto further external data carriers,\n• the use of output data, files, database elements or documents to produce more than individual copies or reproductions,\n• use and transfer of output data, files, database elements or documents to produce systematic collections or databases,\n• the use of output data, files, database elements or documents for commercial purposes that extend beyond the purpose of the contract, specifically their sale\n\nis prohibited.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n9. Prohibited activities; User content\n\n9.1 Irrespective of any potential breach of the law, users are particularly prohibited from pursuing the following activities in the course of all their activities related to Ykings, and specifically when posting content or when engaged in communication:\n\n• Dissemination of viruses, Trojans and other malware;\n• Sending junk or spam mails or chain letters;\n• Propagating or communicating content of an obscene, objectionable, sexual or defamatory nature or content that is likely to (explicitly or implicitly) promote or support racism, fanaticism, hatred, violence or illegal activities;\n• Requesting other users to reveal passwords or personal data for commercial, ille-gal or unlawful purposes;\n• Harassment of other users, e.g. by repeated personal contact without, or contrary to, the response of the other party, and support or promotion of such harassment.\n\n9.2 You grant us an ordinary (non-exclusive), permanent, transferable and sublicenseable right to use the data transferred by you while using Ykings, specifically any completed workouts and uploaded photographs posted by you, on the Ykings website and for communication to the other users.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n10. Authorization of access and users’ responsibilities for access data\n\n10.1 Access is password-protected under remote data transmission, using the access data assigned to you. During registration as described in Section 4 above, you must enter your email address and a password in the input screen of the registration form. Once your user account is activated, the access data enables you to log into your account with your personal profile and start training and/or making use of the products and services provided.\n\n10.2 You undertake to keep your access data and passwords secret and to refrain from providing them to unauthorized third parties. Users must ensure that their access and their use of the available services are only used by them personally. If users become aware of misuse of access data or passwords, they must immediately put a stop to the misuse and inform us by emailing support@ykings.com. In cases of misuse, we are entitled to block the access, with prior warning where applicable. Users are liable for all use and/or other activity carried out under their access data and for any misuse for which they are responsible under statutory provisions.\n\n10.3 Users undertake to keep their data including contact details up-to-date. If these de-tails change during the term of the contract, users must immediately correct the de-tails in their personal settings on the website. If they are unable to do so, they must immediately email their new details to support@ykings.com.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n11. Blocking user access\n\n11.1 Ykings is entitled to block access of a user temporarily or permanently in cases of concrete indication that the user in question has breached these T&amp;Cs and/or ap-plicable law or where Ykings has other justified interest in blocking the access. In making the decision to block an account, Ykings will take the user’s justified interests into adequate consideration.\n\n11.2 In the case of a temporary or permanent block, Ykings will block the user’s access and notify the user of the block by email.\n\n11.3 In the case of a temporary block, Ykings will reactivate the access authorization after the blocking period is over and will notify the user of the reactivation by email. Permanently blocked accounts cannot be reactivated. Permanently blocked persons may not re-register with Ykings.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n12. Technical requirements; user’s obligation to perform data backup\n\n12.1 Users are responsible for the establishment and maintenance of the necessary tech-nical preconditions within their sphere of responsibility in order to avail of Ykings’ ser-vices in accordance with the contract. This applies particularly to the necessary hardware (smartphone and/or tablet) with Android or iOS operating system software, and to an Internet connection with appropriate browser software. Users are responsible for telecommunication costs for their online connection.\n\n12.2 Users undertake to take all appropriate precautions to back up their data, specifically by running regular data backups and by using up-to-date anti-virus software.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n13. Right of cancellation\n\nAll customers that are consumers within the meaning of Section 13 German Civil Code (BGB) (see also Section 3.2 of these T&amp;Cs) are entitled to withdraw the contract declaration they have made to us in accordance with the following Notice of Cancellation and to return the goods.\n\nNotice of Cancellation\n\nRight of cancellation:\n\nYou have the right to cancel the contract within fourteen days without giving rea-sons. The cancellation period is fourteen days from the date of conclusion of the contract.\n\nTo exercise your right of cancellation, you must inform us:\n\nYkings GmbH\nSchöllerstr. 13\n72160 Horb am Neckar\nTelephone +49 (0)89-20317866,\nEmail: support@Ykings.com\n\nof your decision to cancel the contract in a clear declaration (e.g. a letter sent by post, a fax or email). To do so, you can use the attached standard cancellation form; however, use of the form is not obligatory. Timely dispatch of your statement exercising your right of cancellation (i.e. before expiry of the cancellation period) is deemed sufficient for compliance with the cancellation period.\n\nConsequences of cancellation\n\nIf you cancel the contract, we undertake to reimburse you for all payments re-ceived from you, including delivery costs (with the exception of any extra costs arising from your choice of a form of delivery other than our cheapest offer of standard delivery method), immediately and within fourteen days of the date of our receipt of your notice of cancellation at the latest. Reimbursements will be made using the same payment method used by you for the original transaction unless otherwise expressly agreed with you; we do not charge you for these reim-bursements.\n\nIf you have requested that services start within the cancellation period, you under-take to pay us an appropriate pro rata amount for our provision of services during the period up to the date when you notified us of your cancellation; this amount represents an appropriate proportion of the total amount due for provision of the services described in the contract.\n\nStandard cancellation form\nTo make cancellation as simple as possible for you and avoid any queries or other issues, we provide the following standard cancellation form for your cancellation.\n(To cancel the contract, please complete the form and return to us.)\n- To Ykings GmbH\nSchöllerstr.13\n72160 Horb am Neckar, Germany\nsupport@Ykings.com\n<strong>- I/we (*) hereby cancel the contract concluded by me/us (*) over purchase of the following products (*)/provision of the following services (*)</strong>\n\n<strong>- Ordered on (*)/ Received on (*)</strong>\n\n<strong>- Name of consumer(s)</strong>\n\n<strong>- Address of consumer(s)</strong>\n\n<strong>- Signature(s) of consumer(s) (only for cancellations sent on paper)</strong>\n\n<strong>- Date</strong>\n\n<strong>(*) Cross out alternatives that do not apply</strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\nExpiry of the right of cancellation\nThe right of cancellation of a contract for the provision of services expires if provision of the services has been completed or has commenced after your express agreement to said completion or commencement and after your simultaneous confirmation of your awareness that you lose your right to cancellation upon our fulfilment of the contract in full.\nThe right of cancellation of a contract for the supply of digital content not residing on a physical data carrier expires if fulfilment of the contract has commenced after your express agreement to said fulfilment and after your simultaneous confirmation of your awareness that you lose your right to cancellation upon commencement of fulfilment of the contract.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n14. Liability for faults or defects\n\nIn the case of faults or defects in our products or services, you are entitled to the statutory rights and claims, subject to the following limitations of liability as stated in Section 15 below.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n15. Liability\n\n15.1 Liability in the case of free products / services\n\nIn the case of free products or services, our liability extends to the statutory provisions.\n\n15.2 Liability for paid products or services\n\n15.2.1 In the case of paid products or services – irrespective of the legal basis – we are liable for claims for damages or for reimbursement of wasted expenditure within the meaning of Section 284 German Commercial Code (BGB), pursuant to the following provisions listed under 15.2.1 to 15.2.6:\n\n15.2.2 Pursuant to the statutory provisions, we have unlimited liability for damage to life, limb or health, for damages based on intent or gross negligence and for damages falling under the scope of any guarantee or warranty concerning quality or durability unless otherwise stated in the respective warranty agreement.\n\n15.2.3 For all damages other than those stated in Section 15.2.2 based on breach of cardi-nal obligations due to minor negligence, the scope of our liability is limited to com-pensation for foreseeable damages typical of the contract. Cardinal obligations within the meaning of No 1 comprise obligations whose breach endangers fulfilment of the contractual purpose, whose fulfilment constitutes a condition sine qua non, and on the fulfilment of which the Customer regularly relies.\n\n15.2.4 Otherwise any further liability for damage other than that given in Section 15.2.2, based on breach of obligations other than those given in Section 15.2.3 due to minor negligence, is excluded.\n\n15.2.5 Liability under the German Product Liability Act remains unaffected.\n\n15.2.6 The liability provisions above also apply to personal liability on the part of our em-ployees, agents, legal representatives and bodies.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n16. Term of contract and termination\n\n16.1 Contract for the use of free products / services\n\n16.1.1 The contract for use of free products / services runs for an indefinite period.\n\n16.1.2 You can terminate the contract for use of free products / services at any time without giving reasons and delete your user account. To do so, simply enter the appropriate settings in your profile. Please note that when your account is deleted all content and workout information posted by you may or will be deleted by us and that you can no longer access any content already acquired.\n\n16.1.3 We are entitled to terminate the contract for use of free products / services with a termination period of two (2) weeks without giving reasons. Termination is issued in writing.\n\n16.2 Contract for the use of paid products / services\n\n16.2.1 The contract for the use of paid services within the scope of a subscription is con-cluded for a minimum period of 3, 6 or 12 months.\n\n16.2.2 The contract is automatically extended for one further year unless terminated by either party before expiry of the contract term, with a termination period of four weeks. To terminate the contract, enter the appropriate settings in your profile, send an email to support@Ykings.com or notify us of termination by post. Your account will continue to exist after termination of your subscription. We may terminate the contract in written form, particularly by sending an email to the email address stored by you in your user account.\n\n16.3 Right of termination for cause\n\nThe right of termination for cause remains unaffected. In particular, we are entitled to terminate the contract with immediate effect and delete your user account if you breach these T&amp;Cs and/or applicable law. This termination may be preceded by a warning where applicable.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n17. Applicable law\n\nThe law of the Federal Republic of Germany shall apply exclusively, with the excep-tion of the rules that refer to another jurisdiction. Application of the UN Convention on Contracts for the Sale of Goods (CISG) is expressly excluded. Statutory provisions limiting the choice of law and applying mandatory standards, particularly those of the state in which the consumer has his habitual place of residence, shall remain unaffected.', 'Terms of Use', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'terms-of-use', '', '', '2015-10-27 09:03:55', '2015-10-27 09:03:55', '', 0, 'http://192.168.1.76/Projects/ykings/?page_id=649', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(652, 1, '2015-10-27 09:04:08', '2015-10-27 09:04:08', '<strong>Ykings Data Privacy Policy </strong>\n\nAs at: 21.01.2016\n\n&nbsp;\n\nWe want you to feel secure when you visit our website. To ensure this is the case, we comply with the provisions of the German Data Protection Act (BDSG) and the German Telemedia Act (TMG).\n\n&nbsp;\n\nIn this Data Privacy Policy we inform you about which of your personal data are collected, processed and stored by Ykings GmbH. Personal data are individual items of information about the personal or material circumstances of an identified or identifiable natural person. They include information such as your first and last name, postal address, email address, user name selected during the registration process, and password.\n\n&nbsp;\n<ol>\n	<li><strong>Responsible body under the terms of the BDSG</strong></li>\n</ol>\n&nbsp;\n\nThe responsible body under the terms of the BDSG is Ykings GmbH, Schöllerstr. 13, 72160 Horb am Neckar, Germany (hereinafter “Ykings”). For enquiries or questions concerning data protection, you can email us at support@ykings.com.\n\n&nbsp;\n<ol start="2">\n	<li><strong>Collection, processing and use of personal data without registration</strong></li>\n</ol>\n&nbsp;\n\nIf you visit our website without entering any personal data we cannot identify your identity. In this case, we only receive details of the communication process from your browser, without any concrete reference to specific individuals (e.g. IP address). We collect, store and process your data:\n<ul>\n	<li>to enable you to access our website and allow us to perform the services which you use and which are provided on our website,</li>\n	<li>to analyse, adjust and improve our services, content and advertising.</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n<ol start="3">\n	<li><strong>Collection, processing and use of personal data </strong></li>\n</ol>\n&nbsp;\n\nWhen you share your personal data with us while you register and open a customer account, place an order or send us a message, we collect and store these data to the extent necessary for us to perform the contractual services.\n\n&nbsp;\n<ol start="4">\n	<li><strong>Newsletter</strong></li>\n</ol>\n&nbsp;\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width="614">When you sign up to the Ykings Newsletter, you confirm your consent to receiving newsletters and notifications from us that may contain advertising for our own products and services in addition to information about Ykings. You can withdraw your consent to receiving this communication at any time. You can unsubscribe to newsletters and notifications at any time by clicking a link in the e-mail or in your personal settings.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n&nbsp;\n<ol start="5">\n	<li><strong>Transfer of personal data to third parties </strong></li>\n</ol>\n&nbsp;\n\nWe never transfer your personal data to third parties unless you have given prior consent or transfer is permitted by law. In particular, we never transfer your personal data or e-mail address to third parties for advertising purposes or address trading.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nIn some cases we use external service providers for technical (e.g. technical website hosting) or other services. We supply these service providers with personal data only to the extent required for them to perform their services for us. Our external service providers are contractually obliged to comply with data protection and data security regulations.\n\n<strong> </strong>\n<ol start="6">\n	<li><strong>Cookies, web beacons and similar processes</strong></li>\n</ol>\n&nbsp;\n\nWe use cookies, web beacons or similar processes to provide you with a more pleasant experience when you visit our website and to enable you to use specific functions.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nCookies are small files stored to your web access device. They do not contain any personal data. Some of the cookies we use are "session cookies", which are automatically deleted when you end a browser session. Other cookies remain in your computer system and allow us or our partner companies to recognize your browser at your next visit (“persistent cookies”). You can configure your browser to notify you when you receive a cookie and then decide whether to accept it, accept specific cookies only, or refuse to accept cookies altogether. Refusal to accept cookies may impair the range of functions available on our website.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nWeb beacons are small graphic image files (“pixels”) which can be integrated into our website to record user behaviour. Other similar processes include Flash cookies, HTML5 cookies or other local (browser or device-based) storage methods that can – like cookies – store data in your browser or device to recognise your browser or device on your next visit or during a session.\n\n&nbsp;\n<ol start="7">\n	<li><strong>Targeting, tracking, analysis</strong></li>\n</ol>\n&nbsp;\n\nWe use tracking and analysis technologies to collect statistical data about the use of our website and optimise our content and services accordingly. We can also use these technologies to provide content (including advertising) on our own or external websites that is targeted at your interests.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nInformation that is supplied by your browser is collected and evaluated during this process. The data are collected using cookies, web beacons or similar processes (see above, Section 6).\n\n&nbsp;\n\nThe following data may be collected in particular: Address/URL of the website and previous website accessed (“referrer” URL), browser type/version (e.g. Internet Explorer 9), browser language (e.g. German), operating system used (e.g. Windows 8), browser window resolution, monitor resolution, colour depth, Java and Javascript activation, cookies enabled/disabled, abbreviated IP address if applicable, date and time of access.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nAnalysis, tracking and targeting are always performed as anonymised or pseudonymised processes. No user profiles are compiled from your personal data. We may work with external service providers that are authorised to use tracking and analysis technology with our permission. These service providers support us in providing our own content and advertising, and compile anonymised website statistics and analyses for us. We do not permit these service providers to collect personal data from our website for their own purposes.\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\nThis website particularly uses Google Analytics, a web analysis service by Google Inc. ("Google"). Google Analytics uses "cookies", text files that are stored on your computer and allow your use of the website to be analysed. The information about your visit collected by the cookie is generally transferred to a Google server in the USA and saved there. However, if this website has activated IP anonymisation, Google abbreviates your IP address within member states of the European Union or in other signatory states of the Agreement on the European Economic Area. The full IP address will only be transferred to a Google server in the USA and abbreviated there in exceptional cases.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nGoogle will use the information collected on behalf of Ykings to evaluate your use of the website, to compile reports about your activities within this site, and to provide further services for the website operator related to use of the website and Internet use. Google will under no circumstances associate the IP address transmitted by your browser within the operations of Google Analytics with other Google data. You can prevent the installation of cookies by entering the corresponding setting in your browser software. However, please note that in this case you may not be able to use the complete range of functions of this website to their full extent. By using this website you confirm your consent to Google’s processing of the data collected in relation to your visit in the manner described above and for the purpose described above.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nYou can prevent Google Analytics from collecting and using your IP address. To do this, you can install an add-on program for your browser. For a download option and further information, visit <a href="http://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout?hl=de">http://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout?hl=de</a>.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nPlease note that on this website Google Analytics has been extended by the code _anonymizeIp();“ to ensure all IP address evaluation is anonymised.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nFor more information on the Google Analytics terms and conditions of use, visit <a href="http://www.google.com/analytics/terms/de.html">http://www.google.com/analytics/terms/de.html</a> and for information on Google Analytics data privacy policy visit <a href="http://www.google.com/intl/de/analytics/privacyoverview.html">http://www.google.com/intl/de/analytics/privacyoverview.html</a>.\n<ol start="8">\n	<li><strong>Social media plugins</strong></li>\n</ol>\n&nbsp;\n\nWe use social plugins from the following social media providers on our website:\n\n&nbsp;\n<ul>\n	<li>Facebook “Like”: operated by: Facebook Inc., 1601 S. California Ave, Palo Alto, CA 94304, USA.</li>\n	<li>Google+: operated by Google Inc., 1600 Amphitheatre Parkway, Mountain View, CA 94043, USA.</li>\n	<li>Twitter: operated by Twitter, Inc., 795 Folsom St., Suite 600, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA.</li>\n	<li>YouTube, operated by YouTube LLC, domiciled at 901 Cherry Avenue, San Bruno, CA 94066, USA.</li>\n	<li>Pinterest, operated by Pinterest Inc., 808 Brannan Street, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA.</li>\n	<li>Instagram: operated by Instagram Inc., 1601 Willow Road, Menlo Park, California 94025, USA</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\nSocial plugins are software modules developed by social media services which we have integrated into our website. Social plugins use your browser to connect directly to the servers of the social media provider in question. The connection is used to transmit the information to the social media provider that you have accessed our website page containing the social plugin. If you are registered with and logged into the social media provider in question at the time of your visit to our website, the social media provider can assign your visit and your further interaction with the social plugin (e.g. clicking “like”) to your user profile (e.g. your Facebook account). If you are not registered with or logged into the social media provider, the provider may store your IP address.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nTo prevent transmission of this information to the social media service and protect your privacy, we have installed “Shariff”, a privacy solution that only sets up a direct contact between you and the social network when you actively click the Share button. For more information, visit <a href="http://heise.de/-2467514">http://heise.de/-2467514</a> (German) or <a href="https://github.com/heiseonline/shariff">https://github.com/heiseonline/shariff</a> (English).\n\n&nbsp;\n\nFor more information from Facebook about using the plugin and the social media service, visit: http://developers.facebook.com/plugins\n\n&nbsp;\n\nFor more information from Facebook about its data use policy, see:\n\nhttp://www.facebook.com/about/privacy\n\n&nbsp;\n\nFor more information from Google about using the plugin and the social media service, visit:\n\n<a href="https://developers.google.com/+/web/buttons-policy">https://developers.google.com/+/web/buttons-policy</a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\nTwitter’s data privacy information can be viewed at <a href="https://twitter.com/privacy">https://twitter.com/privacy</a>.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nYouTube’s data privacy policy can be viewed at https://www.google.com/policies/privacy.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nPinterest’s data privacy policy can be viewed at https://about.pinterest.com/de/privacy-policy.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nInstagram’s data privacy policy can be viewed at <a href="https://help.instagram.com/155833707900388/">https://help.instagram.com/155833707900388/</a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n<ol start="9">\n	<li><strong>Changes to this data privacy policy</strong></li>\n</ol>\n&nbsp;\n\nYkings retain the right to change this data privacy policy in the future, particularly where Ykings adds to or modifies the services it provides or where changes to the law necessitate amendment of this data privacy policy.\n\n&nbsp;', 'Privacy Policy', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'private-policy', '', '', '2015-10-27 09:04:08', '2015-10-27 09:04:08', '', 0, 'http://192.168.1.76/Projects/ykings/?page_id=652', 0, 'page', '', 0),
