(888, 1, '2016-02-28 10:44:20', '2016-02-28 10:44:20', '<strong>After reading this article you will know</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>what HIIT is and what it does for you</li>\n	<li>why HIIT works for every fitness level</li>\n	<li>how pro-athletes use HIIT to train effectively</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\nHigh-intensity interval training describes any workout that alternates between intense bursts of activity and fixed periods of less-intense activity or even complete rest. HIIT can be a workout regimen or a jogging/sprint interval option. This type of training gets and keeps your heart rate up. HIIT-workouts makes resistance training a lot tougher while increasing your fitness overall. What makes HIIT so effective is the so called afterburn effect. It is the number one reason why HIIT is the best alternative to burn fat in less time.  After you finished your HIIT, you will burn more fat and calories than with regular aerobic and steady-state workouts during your regeneration and rest phase. Hence, HIIT is very important to get fit and athletic in the beginning, but also to get lean and ripped if you are an advanced athlete.\n\nThere is two forms of utilizing HIIT. On one hand there are HIIT-workouts which most of the time can be done at home and consists of full body exercises. On the other hand there are HIIT-runs which are timed intervals for running. At Ykings you can replace the one with the other to be in control of your training. Just don''t skip it.\n\nA good HIIT workout starts with a well-rounded warmup. The high intensity intervals should be performed at near maximum effort and the recovery intervals in a comfortable effort. A real advantage of HIIT is that it is fully adjustable to a person''s needs. Independent of fitness level you could always make it challenging for the particular athlete. Let''s have a look at the 30/30 HIIT-run regimen with four full rounds for a total of 12 minutes. In its original layout you would do a light jogging pace for 30 seconds and the go for 30 seconds sprinting, however if you are not quite there yet, walk instead of jogging and jog instead of sprinting. This is how you could easily adjust HIIT to your own purpose and fitness level. No excuses, get it done.\n<ul>\n	<li>Minutes 1-4 (Warm-Up) - Jog at a comfortable level</li>\n	<li>Minute 5 (Workout Interval 1) Jog/Walk 30 seconds</li>\n	<li>Sprint/Jog 30 seconds at maximum effort</li>\n	<li>Minute 6 (Workout Interval 2) Jog/Walk 30 seconds</li>\n	<li>Sprint/Jog 30 seconds at maximum effort</li>\n	<li>Minute 7 (Workout Interval 3) Jog/Walk 30 seconds</li>\n	<li>Sprint/Jog 30 seconds at maximum effort</li>\n	<li>Minute 8 (Workout Interval 4) Jog/Walk 30 seconds</li>\n	<li>Sprint/Jog 30 seconds at maximum effort</li>\n	<li>Minutes 9-12 (Cool-Down) - Jog at a comfortable level</li>\n</ul>\nMany Pro-athletes and celebrities use HIIT as their preferred option to cut weight in no time. Diligent work ethics doing the HIIT is what makes pro athletes a pro athlete. To be more exact, pros keep their maximum speed at all times during the high intense interval. This means that it is advantageous on a scale of 1-10 (where is 5 standard jogging and 10 is maximum speed) to switch to a speed of 8 or 9 to allow you to perform the interval with the best effort. Additionally some athletes might like the idea of doing the sprints at a slight incline up a hill. The optimal HIIT is achieved when you feel a slight burning in your body after the workout. Last but not least you have to pay attention to the underground and safety. We recommend joint-gentle surfaces like tartan tracks and paths in the forest. Caution on rainy days and when paths are covered with leaves, snow and pebbles.\n\nWhat about you? Do you like HIIT? Any tips to share? Let us know.\n\nPS: In one of our next articles, we will cover HIIT even in more depth and list all the benefits of HIIT.\n\n<strong><em>Ykings is a full body training concept that teaches elite skills and epic body moves. One of our principles at Ykings is that we believe HIIT gets the best out of you in the shortest time. The efficiency of HIIT is the reason why you will find HIIT-runs as well as HIIT-strength workouts in our workout portfolio. Depending on your personal goals and fitness level, HIIT will play a crucial factor to get you either in shape and learn all bodyweight training skills or elevate your arsenal as you reach new levels. </em></strong>\n\n#StriveForProgress\n\n&nbsp;', 'How to utilize High Intensity Interval Training (HIIT)', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'all-about-high-intensity-interval-training-hiit', '', '', '2016-02-28 10:44:20', '2016-02-28 10:44:20', '', 0, 'http://stage.ykings.com/?p=888', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(890, 1, '2016-01-05 14:16:30', '2016-01-05 14:16:30', '<strong>After reading this article you will know</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>what the benefits from HIIT are</li>\n	<li>why HIIT is popular</li>\n	<li>pre-HIIT - what “base fitness level” is</li>\n</ul>\nHIIT training can easily be modified for people of all fitness levels and special conditions, including overweight and diabetes. HIIT workouts can be performed on cycling, swimming, aqua training, jogging or sprinting, just to name a few.\n\nIn the last 2 years, fitness enthusiasts have put their heart rate monitors, essential for cardio workout on the shelves, with the advance of HIIT. Whilst the proven theory for cardio workout has been “more is more” for sustained fat loss, HIIT on the contrary, consists of short bouts of all-out efforts alternating with stretches of recovery. Shorter work out sessions combined with rest for crazy fat loss? Yes. You read that right. However, one will actually be working much harder than the guy on the nearby treadmill. No surprise that many reports have strongly indicated undeniable results from HIIT. HIIT tend to burn more calories than traditional workouts, especially afterward. The post-exercise period is called “EPOC” - Excess Post-exercise Oxygen Consumption. This is generally about a 2-hour period after training where the body is restoring itself to pre-exercise levels, and thus using more energy. Because of the vigorous nature of HIIT workouts, the EPOC generally tends to be higher, adding about 6 to 15% more calories to the overall workout energy expenditure.\n\nHIIT training has been shown to improve:\n<ul>\n	<li>metabolism</li>\n	<li>blood pressure</li>\n	<li>cardiovascular health</li>\n	<li>insulin sensitivity (helps exercising muscles more readily use glucose to make energy)</li>\n	<li>cholesterol profiles</li>\n	<li>abdominal fat and body weight while maintaining muscle mass.</li>\n</ul>\nPrior to beginning HIIT training, you are recommended to establish a foundational level of fitness – a “base fitness level”, which can be consistent aerobic training (3 to 5 times a week for 20 to 60 min per session) for several weeks. This helps promote muscular adaptations - improving oxygen transport to the muscles. Establishing appropriate exercise form and muscle strength are important before engaging in regular HIIT to reduce the risk of musculoskeletal injury.\n\nRegardless of age, gender and fitness level, one of the keys to optimal participation of HIIT training is to modify the intensity of the work interval to a preferred challenging level. This is where your Virtual Coach plays a crucial role in finding your own optimal training intensities as opposed to you simply trying to keep up with the Peers.', 'HIIT - The benefits of HIGH INTENSITY INTERVAL TRAINING', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'hiit-the-benefits-of-high-intensity-interval-training', '', '', '2016-01-05 14:16:30', '2016-01-05 14:16:30', '', 0, 'http://stage.ykings.com/?p=890', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(892, 1, '2015-12-29 11:14:59', '2015-12-29 11:14:59', '<strong>After reading this article you will know</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li><b><strong>which advantages bodyweight exercises have</strong></b></li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>the reasons to focus on bodyweight exercises</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>why you won’t need additional equipment or a gym membership in the future</strong></li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong><u>What are bodyweight exercises?</u></strong>\n\nThese exercises do not use free weights or any other type of machine or equipment. Instead, the person exercising uses his or her own bodyweight as the sole form of resistance for the workout.\n\n<strong><u>Why you should focus on bodyweight exercises.</u></strong>\n\nBodyweight exercises are the roots of fitness. Bodyweight exercises can be a great choice for gaining strength, building muscle, boosting cardiovascular fitness and losing weight. Bodyweight exercises are some of the most common and beneficial exercises that you can do and we will explore the advantages in more detail.\n<ol>\n	<li><em> Super-efficient workouts.</em> The days of two-hour workouts are numbered. Research suggests high-output, bodyweight-based exercises such as Ykings yield awesome fitness gains in very short workout durations. Since there''s no equipment involved, bodyweight workouts make it easy to transition quickly from one exercise to the next. Shorter rest times mean it''s easy to quickly boost heart rate and burn some serious calories.</li>\n	<li><em> Combined HIIT and strength training.</em> Pressed for time but need to hit cardio and strength in one quick workout? Performing quick bodyweight HIIT optimized strength workouts or isolated HIIT-runs will keep the heart pumping while still encouraging muscle and strength development.</li>\n	<li><em> Fast fat-burning.</em> Looking to shed a few unwanted pounds? Just a few minutes of a bodyweight circuit training or a good HIIT (High Intensity Interval Training) can have a major impact on the body''s metabolism. Don''t believe it? Do a run with intervals or try adding a few quick sets of these amped-up burpees into any workout routine and see what happens!</li>\n	<li><em> Something for everyone.</em> Bodyweight exercises are a great choice because they''re easily modified to challenge any fitness level. Adding natural extra resistance, performing the exercises faster or super-slow, and perfecting form are a few ways to make even the simplest exercise more challenging.</li>\n	<li><em> Improved core strength.</em> The "core" is more than just abs. In fact, at least twenty-nine muscles make up the human core, and many simple bodyweight movements can be used to engage all of them. Such exercises improve core strength for better posture and overall health.</li>\n	<li><em> Increased flexibility.</em> Not everyone who does regular resistance training has to end up with tight muscles, inflexible joints and a bad case of imaginary lat syndrome. Bodyweight training for strength and flexibility can go hand-in-hand. Completing bodyweight exercises through a full range of motion is a great way to ensure joints are moving freely, can lead to improved posture and might even reduce the chance of exercise-related injury. And yoga, the bodyweight-based workout of choice for many, is another great way to improve flexibility while also significantly improving strength.</li>\n	<li><em> Convenience.</em> Ask someone why they don''t exercise, and chances are "no time" or "inconvenience" might come up as culprits. Bodyweight workouts can be used as a stress relieving break for those working from home or can provide a great hotel room workout for those on the road. “No time” really becomes no excuse. Anywhere &amp; anytime are your new best friends.</li>\n	<li><em> Better balance.</em> Since bodyweight exercises use no weights, increasing resistance is accomplished in other ways. For example, a regular bodyweight squat can be ramped up by working for pistols (single leg-squat). Super-functional and advanced exercises such as pistols, the human flag or the front lever improve balance through increased body awareness and control. These advantages are another reason why bodyweight exercises improve athletic performance.</li>\n	<li><em> Bye bye, boredom.</em> It can be easy to get stuck in a workout rut of bench presses, lat pull-downs and biceps curls or be bored with the location. That''s why bodyweight training can be so refreshing: It gives you options to spice up any workout routine and can be performed inside or outdoors, alone or with a group of friends, which is particularly enjoyable if some seemingly silly exercises are incorporated into the routine! A little laughter makes the process more enjoyable.</li>\n	<li><em> Cost-efficient.</em> Simply put, gym memberships can be pricey, but bodyweight training is free. Experts cite the low cost of bodyweight training as a key part of its resurgence in popularity. All you need is a proper workout plan. Still don’t know how to get started – Check out the Ykings fitness concept.</li>\n</ol>', 'All about bodyweight exercises', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', '__trashed', '', '', '2016-06-01 10:14:44', '2016-06-01 10:14:44', '', 0, 'http://stage.ykings.com/?p=892', 0, 'post', '', 0),
