(1003, 1, '2016-01-11 08:17:01', '2016-01-11 08:17:01', '<strong>After reading this article you will know</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>where calisthenics and street workout fit in the movement culture</strong></li>\n	<li><strong>what you have to focus on entering the movement arena</strong></li>\n	<li><strong>how your mind and strength helps to control your body</strong></li>\n</ul>\nMany modern athletes forgot about the importance of movement. These days the importance shifts back and you can witness it already in various sports. Take a look at MMA fighters, many of them have movement coaches who make them faster, more powerful and overall better fighters. Urban gymnastics also known as street workout or calisthenics is very popular and people get back to learn elite static gymnastic skills from scratch. The movement culture is embedded in yoga, capoeira but also in calisthenics. For those of you who do calisthenics professionally, a broader focus on the movement culture can help tremendously to come up with new skills and moves for your freestyle sessions. The movement culture is the new paradigm shift in fitness. Vivid proof of that is the popularity of sports such as functional training, crossfit and yoga.\n\n<a href="http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/4866138077_f101833817_o.jpg" rel="attachment wp-att-1004"><img class="size-large wp-image-1004" src="http://ykings.com/New/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/4866138077_f101833817_o-1024x683.jpg" alt="A group of men and women practice capoeira on the beach in Dili, Timor-Leste, preparing for upcoming events such as International Youth Day, 12 August." width="1024" height="683" /></a>\n\nMovement is liquid and two elements that get you started are quality work on your flexibility and mobility. These two will help to gradually develop your strength and skill level. In today''s civilized world flexibility and mobility have become a core problem. Just think about how many hours a day you spent on just sitting? So if you want to spent some more time taking control of and creating awareness over your body, you should give your health a higher priority. The simple rule is to invest a good portion of time in your health; otherwise you will spend the same amount of time later on your illness.\n\nBuilding a strong body requires a clear and dedicated mindset. Your mind builds your strength which leads to your goals and perform those moves. Before evolving to a master of body control you will have to get more flexibile and find your balance. All the power of a body centered lifestyle comes from your core.  If you are up for it, you are already in the right place. Learn, evolve, master!\n\nYkings helps you to get a foot into the world of movement. The progression formula secures your gradual development to achieve better body awareness and epic body skills. Join a community of like-minded and start your own journey.\n\nPS: In one of our next articles we will cover in which way you will not need any rest days.', 'How to enter the world of movement', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-to-enter-the-world-of-movement', '', '', '2016-01-11 08:17:01', '2016-01-11 08:17:01', '', 0, 'http://stage.ykings.com/?p=1003', 0, 'post', '', 2),
