(1064, 1, '2016-01-25 14:38:18', '2016-01-25 14:38:18', 'After reading this article you will know\n<ul>\n	<li>why stretching should be a workout priority</li>\n	<li>the benefits of stretching especially when learning calisthenics</li>\n	<li>that stretching is a mind and muscle balancing tool</li>\n</ul>\nStretching is probably the most underrated part of a complete workout. Although stretching is the most natural and automatic action of people when waking up and after hours of inactivity, it is still skipped regularly by a lot of athletes. Regular stretching routines are far less emphasized by many, but they are just as important as your workouts. The topic is overall somewhat controversial and study results are split on various subtopics. We recommend giving a good stretching routine a higher priority in your workouts, especially when you get started to do more advanced functional training and tap into the world of calisthenics and gymnastics.\n\nStarting to learn the moves and skills of gymnastics and street workout, a certain degree of flexibility and range of motion is required. Our experience has shown that those athletes we trained that dedicated more time and effort in stretching improved faster with their progressions while also developing a good posture. An increase in flexibility is accompanied by improved balance, coordination, fluidity and speed. These elements need to be well developed if you want to move up the ladder with calisthenics skills. While it is still widely debated as to whether or not stretching can help prevent injury, it has been proven to help increase blood flow to the muscles, thereby possibly reducing muscle soreness and speeding up the recovery process. Calisthenics is the sport of progression and strength. Strength workouts consume a lot of your energy, so there are high incentives to overcome that energy depletion in a healthy way. In other words…..stretch!\n\nEach of us is prone to fall out of balance in our own way. But as with most things in life we need balance to simply feel better. What has that to do with stretching? While strength exercises will shorten your muscles, stretching your muscles will make them longer and more flexible. Understand stretching as the perfect balancing tool to your hard training. The same holds true for your mindset. Stretching in its most sophisticated form is yoga and you can’t deny the point that a good stretching routine will allow your body to recharge while your mind is calm. Make use of the mental break and listen to your body. Finally use a good stretching routine on rest days if you like want to benefit your recovery. Put in perspective, stretching helps your mind and body to have a more balanced training effect; getting you even faster to your goals.\n\nWhich priority have you given stretching up to now? Ever considered to incorporate them in your workout regularly? Tell us more about your experiences and leave a comment to join the discussion with us.\n\nPS: In our next article on this topic, we will cover how and when to incorporate stretching in your workouts.\n\n<strong><em>Ykings is a full body training concept that teaches elite skills and epic body moves from competitive gymnastics to calisthenics. Our in-app coaching function and progression formula integrates not only your skill level in the workouts, it also includes dynamic warmup sessions and good structured stretching routines. Join the Ykings family and get guided step by step with perfect tailored workout plans.</em></strong>', 'How stretching influences your training - stretching essentials part 1', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-stretching-influences-your-training-stretching-essentials-part-1', '', '', '2016-01-25 14:38:18', '2016-01-25 14:38:18', '', 0, 'http://ykings.com/?p=1064', 0, 'post', '', 0),
