(1081, 1, '2016-02-08 07:21:34', '2016-02-08 07:21:34', 'After reading this article you will know\n<ul>\n	<li>what mental strength is all about</li>\n	<li>how to develop your mental strength</li>\n	<li>how to start a new mental thought process</li>\n</ul>\nMental strength is the ability to create <u>healthy habits</u> to consistently perform toward the upper range of your potential and talent regardless of environmental circumstances. Mentally strong people have clear visions and know how to <u>manage their emotions, thoughts, and behaviors</u> in ways that set them up for success in life as well as in sports. Mental strength influences your motivation to win, endurance to be tough and your healthy state of mind in sports and in life. To develop your mental strength you have to <u>challenge your current beliefs</u> and <u>open up for new ideas</u>. Think about the following concepts and make them work for you, to enjoy a new way of thinking.\n\n<strong>Be positive</strong>- life isn’t always easy and fair, however “When the going gets tough, the tough get going”. A good way to stay positive is to have your goals always in the back of your mind. Anytime you catch yourself slacking, questioning your motivation, or feeling like you want to quit, repeat your personal goals and tell yourself what you are doing this for. Learn to see negativity as a waste of time. Give it no room and crush it anytime it starts to come back.\n\n<strong>Be in control</strong> - stop complaining and feeling sorry for you. Either change it or leave it. Recognize that most of the time you are in control of the situation. All it takes is your attitude. Is failure a win or a devastating loss? The day you see failure as a reason to try again and push harder, you have learned a big lesson. Use failure as an opportunity to grow and improve. Stay in the game and develop the will to keep trying until you get it right.\n\n<strong>Be change</strong> – get out of your comfort zone. Most people are afraid of change. They love to stay in security and in their comfort zone. Understand that change is inevitable and believe in your abilities to adapt. The magic happens outside your comfort zone. So get out there and take on the challenge.\n\n<strong>Be focused</strong> - live for the present and plan for the future. Accept responsibility of your behavior and learn from past mistakes. Think about the most efficient way to tackle a problem and once you find it, stick to it. Eliminate non-sense and guide your attention to the important tasks.\n\n<strong>Be patient</strong> – develop a growth mindset and enjoy the little things. Apply your skills and time to the best of your ability and understand that real change takes time. Admit your shortcoming and continually strive to improve. Moreover focus to celebrate small wins and progress, knowing that you are continuing to improve if you be patient with yourself. #StriveForProgress.\n\nIf you master these thinking patterns you will be able to visualize and achieve your goals. It will show in every new workout week and on each training day. Moreover you will have developed a mental toughness to endure and persevere, a mindset that keeps you going when others give up. Get into a mode of being done with the workout mentally. If you can see it, you can do it.\n\nHave your workouts been a torture? How have you overcome the struggle? Is a little bit of anxiety before each workout healthy? Tell us more about your experiences and leave a comment to join the discussion with us.\n\n<strong><em>Ykings is a full body training concept that teaches elite skills and epic body moves of competitive gymnastics and calisthenics. Our in-app coaching function and progression formula integrates not only your skill level in the workouts; it connects you also to a like-minded community. Stay positive and motivated with the Ykings family and get guided step by step with perfect tailored workout plans.</em></strong>', 'The importance of mental strength in sports &amp; how to build it', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-importance-of-mental-strength-in-sports-how-to-build-it', '', '', '2016-02-08 07:21:34', '2016-02-08 07:21:34', '', 0, 'http://ykings.com/?p=1081', 0, 'post', '', 2),
