(1181, 1, '2016-03-22 20:43:53', '2016-03-22 20:43:53', '<em>After reading this article you will know</em>\n<ul>\n	<li><em>why workout programs are like diets</em></li>\n	<li><em>what most workout programs are lacking</em></li>\n	<li><em>why you should engage in a workout concept for long-term success</em></li>\n</ul>\nA workout program is a pre-defined regimen of sport exercises that holds a claim of achieving a fitness goal in a specific amount of time. Many workout programs get people the wanted results but as many are also not able to keep the results for long. In this article we want to turn our attention to the problem with workout programs and which alternatives you should consider choosing the right option for you.\n\nIf you have ever finished a workout program, then you most certainly came across the feeling of either pure joy or asking yourself what you should do next. Your options are simple, either keep doing the current workout program or find a more suitable alternative. While the first option could get boring over time, the other is a painful job of research. How to stay in shape is the remaining question.\n\nLook for alternatives that are sustainable and require your consistent effort. Don’t fall for workout programs which enjoy the same pattern like diets. Diets and workout programs often don’t generate the wished long term benefits. Your body just doesn’t respond so well to short changes of what has been different for your whole life. Change is a process over time and a constant effort to make it a habit. You as a person will have to make time for the training and your body will need time to adjust to it. Most people expect great results in a short period of time and fall for workout programs that get you fit, but don’t have anything else to offer and don’t teach you how to stay in shape. The follow up is what most programs are lacking. After the workout, is before the workout.\n\nTo make things easier, we recommend taking a look at workout concepts which give you long, mid and short term goals and a variety of different training stimuli. Only working through a workout program once will not do the trick. A workout concept on the other hand is characterized by individuality. A good workout concept should be able to personalize your training, regardless of fitness level and contain multiple goals in several fields such as agility, strength, mobility, skills, movement and so on. Understand a workout concept as a process of constant personal improvement. If you can either combine it in a beneficial way with your favorite sport or embed it in your life you will never look back.\n\nHow did you feel after you finished a whole x-weeks workout program? Have you achieved your goals? Leave a comment and let us know.\n\n<strong><em>Ykings is progressive training concept that teaches elite skills and epic body moves. Learn gradually with the well-rounded progression formula and evolve to a new you. Master challenging exercises from gymnastics and bodyweight training</em></strong>\n\n<strong><em>#WeGrowTogether #StriveForProgress</em></strong>', 'The reasons to engage rather with a workout concept than a workout program', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-reasons-to-engage-rather-with-a-workout-concept-than-a-workout-program', '', '', '2016-03-22 20:43:53', '2016-03-22 20:43:53', '', 0, 'http://ykings.com/?p=1181', 0, 'post', '', 0),
