(1355, 1, '2016-06-01 12:26:17', '2016-06-01 12:26:17', 'Hey everyone I am Michael,\r\n\r\nafter 4 years of reppin‘ the same weights over and over again I became tired of spending my time in the gym for a little progress. Missing goals, lacking motivation and searching for alternative training methods I got in touch with calisthenics. Calisthenics in its purest form combines raw strength and freestyle elements with almost endless variations. So I stopped focusing on how much weight I could bench and started with the basic body weight exercises and some freestyle moves. Spending time getting strong and skilled I fell in love with calisthenics and I am currently in the best shape of my life.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_1124" align="aligncenter" width="675"]<a href="http://ykings.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/IMG_3954-e1455807835740.jpg" rel="attachment wp-att-1124"><img class=" wp-image-1124" src="http://ykings.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/IMG_3954-1024x768.jpg" alt="Bruce Lee''s favourite abs exercise - the dragon flag" width="675" height="506" /></a> Bruce Lee''s favourite abs exercise - the dragon flag[/caption]\r\n\r\nLooking forward I am excited to work with Team Ykings to bring the sport into the spotlight. I am currently on my way to Planche, however my personal favourite are still all kinds of strength elements. I am also working on some other cool moves and can''t wait to unlock them increased overall strength. If you''re also ambitious enough to do so, follow me in the app and let''s conquer gainsville together.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_1122" align="aligncenter" width="483"]<a href="http://ykings.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/FullSizeRender.jpg" rel="attachment wp-att-1122"><img class=" wp-image-1122" src="http://ykings.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/FullSizeRender-624x1024.jpg" alt="Power Competition @barwarz Berlin +24kg pullups" width="483" height="793" /></a> Power Competition @barwarz Berlin +24kg pullups[/caption]\r\n\r\n<div style="text-align: left;"></div>\r\n<div style="text-align: left;"></div>\r\n<div style="text-align: left;">\r\n\r\nSpending quality time with my crew (barliner_workout), my motivation comes from working out in the park clearing my mind with a few sets after a stressful day. Sometimes it''s hard to get your ass up, but just remember how awesome it feels when you finish up your final reps and be done with your workout. Even more motivation kicks in when you mastered the next step or nailed a new skill the first time. When it comes to training attituded, consistency and persistance is the name of the game.\r\n\r\nSometimes it''s also the mirror that motivates me. Looking at yourself and realising that you are in full control of how you want to look like is a great feeling. So if you need some motivation and can''t find it, I am here to share some with you!\r\n\r\nP.S. We will not skip leg day, but we can cry together afterwards.\r\n\r\nFind me in the app under micha_bln_\r\n\r\n</div>', 'micha_bln_: It''s all about reps and sets', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'portfolio-1', '', '', '2016-06-10 10:49:49', '2016-06-10 10:49:49', '', 0, 'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=post-portfolio&#038;p=1355', 0, 'post-portfolio', '', 0),
