(1415, 1, '2016-06-08 14:51:45', '2016-06-08 14:51:45', '<div id="cc-m-8363560395" class="j-module n j-text ">\r\n\r\nThe word <strong><i>calisthenics</i></strong> comes from the ancient Greek words <i>kálos</i> (κάλλος), which means "beauty", and <i>sthénos</i> (σθένος), meaning "strength". Calisthenics is raw and pure bodyweight training and also known as Street Workout. One of the greatest advantages of bodyweight training is that you can do it anywhere, anytime, and there are easier and more advanced exercises to start or evolve with.\r\n\r\nBeginners as well as advanced athletes will find a goal to pursue with the sport. Besides the standard claims of many sports and fitness programms, calisthenics does not only increase your general fitness and get you in great shape, but provides multiple benefits in addition for you.\r\n\r\nProper calisthenics training will promote the growth of lean muscle mass, and increase your strength, mobility, flexibility, agility, and endurance.\r\n\r\nAs you see from the list of benefits of the sport, there is a fine line to competitive gymnastics. In the Ykings workout concept we embedded the adaptive nature of the sport in a comprehensive progressive bodyweight training concept. If you want to be more than just fit, let us hunt down skills and evolve you to a bodyweight master. Welcome to our world.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'What is Calisthenics?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'what-is-calisthenics', '', '', '2016-06-08 15:58:35', '2016-06-08 15:58:35', '', 0, 'http://ykings.com/New/?page_id=1415', 0, 'page', '', 0),
