(1447, 1, '2016-06-07 11:49:55', '2016-06-07 11:49:55', 'Ykings includes the most prominent skills of calisthenics, gymnastics and standard bodyweight training. Among others, you will have the opportunity to receive guided training towards skills and moves such as the human flag, front and back lever, L-Sit, handstand, One Arm Pushups and many more.', 'What skill & moves will I learn?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'what-skill-moves-will-i-learn', '', '', '2016-06-07 11:49:55', '2016-06-07 11:49:55', '', 0, 'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=1447', 0, 'ufaq', '', 0),
(1448, 1, '2016-06-07 11:51:16', '2016-06-07 11:51:16', 'Progressive bodyweight training (PBT) is the path to adjust your body and mind gradually for bigger tasks. In PBT you will be guided with gradual steps to master difficult movements and skills. In essence an elite skill is divided into sub-exercises called progressions. Mastering progressions and ultimately your wanted skill over time is what progressive bodyweight training is all about.', 'What is progressive bodyweight training?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'what-is-progressive-bodyweight-training', '', '', '2016-06-07 11:51:16', '2016-06-07 11:51:16', '', 0, 'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=1448', 0, 'ufaq', '', 0),
(1449, 1, '2016-06-07 11:54:26', '2016-06-07 11:54:26', 'The beauty of bodyweight training is that it almost needs no equipment. All you need to start is a pullup bar and at best a set of sturdy parallettes or gymnastic rings. With the smartphone app you will have your workout plan with you anywhere you go. Train alone at home or together with others in one of the many calisthenics parks around you. The required equipment is specified for each workout. All needed equipment can also be substituted by the things you have at home.', 'What kind of equipment is required?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'what-kind-of-equipment-is-required', '', '', '2016-06-07 11:54:26', '2016-06-07 11:54:26', '', 0, 'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=1449', 0, 'ufaq', '', 0),
(1450, 1, '2016-06-07 11:55:59', '2016-06-07 11:55:59', 'If you’re healthy enough to exercise, you can start Ykings. The adaptive nature and the flexibility of the workout concept with its progressions gives athletes of any fitness and skill level a way to start.', 'Am I too old? Too fat? Too inexperienced?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'am-i-too-old-too-fat-too-inexperienced', '', '', '2016-06-07 11:55:59', '2016-06-07 11:55:59', '', 0, 'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=1450', 0, 'ufaq', '', 0),
(1451, 1, '2016-06-07 11:57:15', '2016-06-07 11:57:15', 'In the free version of Ykings you can try multiple workouts, engage with the community and get a feeling what Ykings is all about.\r\n\r\nWe have developed Ykings Pro for those of you, who seek an adaptive workout concept or want to pursue skills while getting strong and fit. Ykings Pro includes the following points:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Access to all workouts, skills, progressions and HIIT runs</li>\r\n 	<li>Weekly workout plans which dynamically adapt to your feedback (availability, workout intensity, skill- and fitness level)</li>\r\n 	<li>Full fletched workout days with warmups, fundamentals (pre-workout), strength &amp;HIIT-strength workouts and stretching routines</li>\r\n 	<li>Special designed skill raids – pick your wanted skill and encounter professional skill trainings to push your progress</li>\r\n 	<li>Progression formula - master elite skills (muscleup, front lever, human flag and more) with essential step by step progressions integrated in your workouts</li>\r\n 	<li>Guidance - all progressions and exercises include video tutorials and pro tips</li>\r\n 	<li>Freestyle function – track your own workout sessions and log them in your profile</li>\r\n 	<li>Ykings Community – receive tips and tricks from other athletes, friends and featured athletes &amp; find athletes and trainings spots close to you</li>\r\n</ul>', 'What is the benefit of Ykings Pro (Coach)?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'what-is-the-benefit-of-ykings-pro-coach', '', '', '2016-06-07 11:57:15', '2016-06-07 11:57:15', '', 0, 'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=1451', 0, 'ufaq', '', 0),
(1452, 1, '2016-06-07 11:58:34', '2016-06-07 11:58:34', 'Sure. Ykings is a workout concept that can be easily combined with other training programs and sports. Ykings will provide you with physical strength and skills that will benefit your performance in other sports and training programs. Just make sure you don’t over train and take the appropriate rest days.', 'Can I combine Ykings with other training programs and sports?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'can-i-combine-ykings-with-other-training-programs-and-sports', '', '', '2016-06-07 11:58:34', '2016-06-07 11:58:34', '', 0, 'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=1452', 0, 'ufaq', '', 0),
(1453, 1, '2016-06-07 11:59:55', '2016-06-07 11:59:55', 'Yes, although Ykings is highly adaptive to your workout needs and is influenced by the goals you pursue, you will build strong lean muscle. Ykings is not about extensive muscle mass like you might expect from bodybuilding. We just build the necessary strength to perform elite moves.', 'Will I build muscle with Ykings?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'will-i-build-muscle-with-ykings', '', '', '2016-06-07 11:59:55', '2016-06-07 11:59:55', '', 0, 'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=1453', 0, 'ufaq', '', 0),
(1454, 1, '2016-06-07 12:02:17', '2016-06-07 12:02:17', 'The tracks are a first indicator for setting up the perfect workout plan for you. Follow a specific track to build different kinds of strength and get in shape to progress. It is totally up to you and you will receive workout plans according to your goals. The power of calisthenics shows in its characteristic goals of being fit and strong, while mastering insane skills.\r\n\r\nChoose lean if you interested in strength endurance\r\n\r\nChoose athletic if you are interested in explosive strength\r\n\r\nChoose strong if you are interested in max. strength', 'What are the focus tracks for?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'what-are-the-focus-tracks-for', '', '', '2016-06-07 12:02:17', '2016-06-07 12:02:17', '', 0, 'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=1454', 0, 'ufaq', '', 0),
(1455, 1, '2016-06-07 12:05:30', '2016-06-07 12:05:30', '<span style="font-family: ''Century Gothic'',''sans-serif'';">As soon as you can perform the current progression as outlined in the workouts and videos, you can activate the next progression and start working on it. In general, the leaner and smaller you are the faster you will progress through calisthenics skills. In average a person advances every 4-6 weeks, assuming consistent and diligent work each week. After all just be very comfortable with the current progression and you will be more than ready to move on.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-family: ''Century Gothic'',''sans-serif'';">Always remember to go back to an earlier progression to relief and finish up the set in case you are not able to finish the set with your newly activated progression.</span>', 'When do I move to the next progression?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'when-do-i-move-to-the-next-progression', '', '', '2016-06-07 12:05:30', '2016-06-07 12:05:30', '', 0, 'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=1455', 0, 'ufaq', '', 0),
(1456, 1, '2016-06-07 12:07:58', '2016-06-07 12:07:58', 'Fundamentals are considered to be a pre-workout. Fundamentals help you to additionally condition and strengthen specific parts of your body and get adjusted to the workouts ahead. There are special fundamentals that focus on mobility, flexibility and very specific basic skill work. Work your way through the regimen each day to hone your skills, perfect each movement and be properly warmed up.', 'What is the purpose of “Fundamentals” in a workout day?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'what-is-the-purpose-of-fundamentals-in-a-workout-day', '', '', '2016-06-07 12:07:58', '2016-06-07 12:07:58', '', 0, 'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=1456', 0, 'ufaq', '', 0),
(1457, 1, '2016-06-07 12:12:54', '2016-06-07 12:12:54', 'Activating a raid on a specific skill will set a priority for that skill/move in your upcoming workout weeks. You will receive special designed skill trainings for the activated raid. Skill trainings are very demanding and will test your willingness to learn the skill. You can activate a raid for an elite skill in your personal “Skills”-section. You will find it in the navigation bar in the apps.', 'What is the “Raid” function and how to activate it?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'what-is-the-raid-function-and-how-to-activate-it', '', '', '2016-06-07 12:12:54', '2016-06-07 12:12:54', '', 0, 'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=1457', 0, 'ufaq', '', 0),
(1458, 1, '2016-06-07 12:13:55', '2016-06-07 12:13:55', 'This is a very individual question and depends on your strength, endurance and level of fitness. In average the workouts take around 35 minutes, considering a solid warmup and stretching routine.', 'How long in average will the workouts take?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'how-long-in-average-will-the-workouts-take', '', '', '2016-06-07 12:13:55', '2016-06-07 12:13:55', '', 0, 'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=1458', 0, 'ufaq', '', 0),
(1459, 1, '2016-06-07 12:15:02', '2016-06-07 12:15:02', 'You will progress fastest and healthiest if you follow the workout days as laid out. In this way we can ensure the most efficient development and avoid overtraining of specific areas in your body. Please take your regeneration phases seriously.', 'Can you switch the order of workout days in the workout plan?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'can-you-switch-the-order-of-workout-days-in-the-workout-plan', '', '', '2016-06-07 12:15:02', '2016-06-07 12:15:02', '', 0, 'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=1459', 0, 'ufaq', '', 0),
(1460, 1, '2016-06-07 12:17:53', '2016-06-07 12:17:53', '<span style="font-family: ''Century Gothic'',''sans-serif'';">Newly activated progressions should be attacked with care. Don’t sacrifice form to do the last repetition. Always watch the video tutorial and check out our blog and brain lab for additional information. Use your already mastered progressions to finish up the set in case you cannot with the new activated progression.</span>', 'How do I handle new activated progressions in my training?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'how-do-i-handle-new-activated-progressions-in-my-training', '', '', '2016-06-07 12:17:53', '2016-06-07 12:17:53', '', 0, 'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=1460', 0, 'ufaq', '', 0),
(1461, 1, '2016-06-07 12:19:57', '2016-06-07 12:19:57', 'Please follow the rule of thumb of taking a rest day in between workout days. For beginners and even advanced athletes we recommend not going beyond 3-4 workout days per week. Progressive bodyweight training is very demanding especially if you are in the midst of mastering a skill. Please read also the question on overtraining, take sufficient rest days and listen to your body at all times.', 'Can I do this every day?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'can-i-do-this-every-day', '', '', '2016-06-07 12:19:57', '2016-06-07 12:19:57', '', 0, 'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=1461', 0, 'ufaq', '', 0),
(1462, 1, '2016-06-07 12:22:33', '2016-06-07 12:22:33', 'It really depends where you starting and where you going. When you start to exercise and getting comfortable with the workouts, you should recognize first changes within the first 3-4 weeks. Assuming your diet is in check as well you will only progress if you are in great shape. Reaching your ultimate fitness is not goal but a given at Ykings. Results and goals are achieved fastest by those athletes who exercise consistently and don’t get injured while doing it. Take your workout days and regeneration phase serious and see for yourself.', 'How soon will I see results?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'how-soon-will-i-see-results', '', '', '2016-06-07 12:22:33', '2016-06-07 12:22:33', '', 0, 'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=ufaq&#038;p=1462', 0, 'ufaq', '', 0);
