(1589, 1, '2016-06-10 11:05:03', '2016-06-10 11:05:03', 'Hi, it’s me, the Koala_Lady!\r\n\r\nAs a start-up Ykings member it is my utmost goal, to motivate all Ykings in their journey of chasing their Calisthenics fitness dream. And what better way to reach that dream than with the help of the Ykings Progression Formula. The perfect step-by-step training method to start smashing goals, exceeding limits and defeating boundaries.\r\n\r\nSo whilst I’ve always been a gym member, I originally began my sporting as a dancer 18 years ago. As a result, I have always been very aware of my body and its capabilities and thus, focused mainly on body control and bodyweight exercises. After a while though, Yoga, Pilates and Freeletics weren’t enough and I was hungry for more. After a good friend asked me to join his Calisthenics Team 9 months ago, I dove into a world of endless goals, challenges and motivation. Calisthenics is not a walk in park. Especially for us girls, it is a very challenging sport. But with a lot of motivation, a little patience and the right training method, it is the most rewarding experience when you realise your progress!\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_991" align="aligncenter" width="342"]<a href="http://ykings.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/6.jpg" rel="attachment wp-att-991"><img class="wp-image-991" src="http://ykings.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/6.jpg" alt="6" width="342" height="514" /></a> Straddle handstand in the park[/caption]\r\n\r\nA lot of people say to me „oh but you’re super fit... I can’t do that!“ Well, I started off 9 months ago thinking exactly the same thing, but what better time to start trying than right now?!\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">„Don’t stop when you’re tired, stop when you’re done!“</p>\r\nMy goals this year are to finally get that first muscle-up and to progress with handstand and balance exercises. What are your goals? Will you make it into the Hall of Fame?  If you want something badly enough, there are no limits to what you can achieve.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_993" align="aligncenter" width="348"]<a href="http://ykings.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/31.jpg" rel="attachment wp-att-993"><img class="wp-image-993" src="http://ykings.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/31.jpg" alt="31" width="348" height="464" /></a> Partner workout at the beach[/caption]\r\n\r\nFollow me in the App under - <strong>Koala_Lady</strong>', 'Koala_Lady: Reach, exceed & defeat!', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'koala_lady-reach-exceed-defeat', '', '', '2016-06-10 11:05:03', '2016-06-10 11:05:03', '', 0, 'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=post-portfolio&#038;p=1589', 0, 'post-portfolio', '', 0),
(1590, 1, '2016-06-10 11:08:10', '2016-06-10 11:08:10', 'Hi I am Dusan,\r\n\r\nand I was always interested in sports of all kinds. Over the years I tried a lot of different things to not only get fit but also to learn something along the way. This is when I found calisthenics.\r\n\r\nYkings combines the major skills and moves from calisthenics, streetworkout and urban gymnastics in a nice dynmaic coaching function. I wish had that back in the day.\r\n\r\nEarly on I struggled with  finding the right sources to get started with the sport. Routines, progressions and a clear guide on what to do were cumbersome to bring together. When I started not only me but also my friends were skeptical.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_999" align="aligncenter" width="630"]<a href="http://ykings.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/File-Jan-08-8-22-26-AM.jpeg" rel="attachment wp-att-999"><img class="wp-image-999" src="http://ykings.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/File-Jan-08-8-22-26-AM.jpeg" alt="File Jan 08, 8 22 26 AM" width="630" height="354" /></a> Human flag in a pedestrians''s tunnel[/caption]\r\n\r\nNone of my friends believed that I could gain some real strength and legit muscle mass doing this sport, however I proved them wrong and so can you! I am following a body-centered mindset that changed my whole perspective of fitness and bodyweight training as a whole.\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>"I''d rather be able to be in full body control than just trying to get fit."</em></p>\r\nWhat about you? What do you want? In this community we are all about progressing with epic moves and skills. Learning, evolving and mastering it. You should join, if you seeking a purposeful training method.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_998" align="aligncenter" width="641"]<a href="http://ykings.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/File-Jan-08-8-21-56-AM.jpeg" rel="attachment wp-att-998"><img class="wp-image-998" src="http://ykings.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/File-Jan-08-8-21-56-AM.jpeg" alt="File Jan 08, 8 21 56 AM" width="641" height="641" /></a> Working out with buddies. Anytime. Anywhere[/caption]\r\n\r\nAfter almost three years of dedicated training I am more motivated than ever before and I have tons of new goals for the year. I want to step my game up in freestyle but also concentrate further on static skills. This being said I post constantly challenges for me and my followers to join. Check me out.\r\n\r\nFollow me in the app - <strong>Dusan</strong>', 'Dusan: Need a challenge? Join me.', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'dusan-need-a-challenge-join-me', '', '', '2016-06-10 11:08:10', '2016-06-10 11:08:10', '', 0, 'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=post-portfolio&#038;p=1590', 0, 'post-portfolio', '', 0),
(1591, 1, '2016-06-10 11:10:38', '2016-06-10 11:10:38', 'Hey I’m kay,\r\nmy fitness journey like many others started in the gym a few years ago, but I never felt challenged enough to really push myself enough until I met a calisthenics team. The training style that I discovered at that time with all the progress and goals got me hooked. I love the idea about not being judged based on how many plates you can lift. I haven’t been back to a gym since.\r\n\r\nThroughout my life I have always stayed relatively fit and healthy, but i never had a passion for a sport. Now i do. Streetworkout has taught me that the possibilities are endless and the team feeling and working out with friends is what keeps me pushing harder even now.\r\n\r\nI couldn’t lift my own body weight before calisthenics and believed it was because I am a female, now I’m very close to attaining my first strict-form muscle up. I have learnt that confidence and determination play a big part in fulfilling my goals. I used to have a fear of handstand which i overcame by being patient, researching various techniques and taking advice from team members.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://ykings.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/IMG-20151112-WA0006-e1455803919747.jpg" rel="attachment wp-att-1120"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-1120" src="http://ykings.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/IMG-20151112-WA0006-1024x576.jpg" alt="IMG-20151112-WA0006" width="1024" height="576" /></a>\r\nThis year my goals are to improve my flexibility helping me achieve a press handstand and improve my strength aas well as overall performance. I will also start my own journey to a flag.\r\n\r\nIf you lack the community, the workout spot and want guidance by pros as well as personalized workout plans and all progressions of the most desireable moves in streetworkout &amp; urban gymnastics, check us out.\r\n\r\nI often receive praise from females who say things like i wish i could do what you do and my response is always the same; you can, if you pace yourself and use your own results as motivation to go harder,\r\nfollow me in the App under - kay_wham', 'kay_wham: Pace yourself & stay motivated to go harder', '', 'draft', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'kay_wham-pace-yourself-stay-motivated-to-go-harder', '', '', '2016-06-10 14:58:22', '2016-06-10 14:58:22', '', 0, 'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=post-portfolio&#038;p=1591', 0, 'post-portfolio', '', 0),
(1592, 1, '2016-06-10 11:13:41', '2016-06-10 11:13:41', 'Hi I am Dom,\r\n\r\nmany of you know me from my youtube channel, but nevertheless I will introduce myself. My whole journey started nine years ago when my brother showed me one of the most inspiring free running videos of Chase &amp; Cole Armitage. Watching those videos, I was able to do a few flips in the beginning on a trampoline and realized that I want to do this for the rest of my life.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://ykings.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/002-e1455812985550.jpg" rel="attachment wp-att-1127"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-1127" src="http://ykings.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/002-1024x645.jpg" alt="002" width="853" height="537" /></a>\r\n\r\nI never had a teacher, never trained gymnastics and had no access to a proper gym. During that time I fell prey to a lot of injuries just because of that. However each injury which felt like a little failure made me realize how much I want this and so it became very important to me. I was so obsessed with free running that all the injuries, all that pain and patience that created many doubts in my mind were absolutely crushed.\r\n\r\nI quickly developed a good skill set and wanted to do other stuff too. I started boxing, I also did some olympic weightlifting and immersed myself with MMA. For a while I wanted to be the best MMA fighter and I even thought about leaving free running to do that. Luckily this was when I heard Ido Portal saying that it''s not about specialization, it''s not about being the best at this or that but being the best you. With your unique mixture and movement variety. That quote literally saved my life and started to form my philosophy. Looking back at all the things I''ve attempted to do made no sense anymore. At that point I stopped trying to be something I''m not and just started being me. I became a mover. My versatility allowed me to discover new moves and patterns and I combined every practise into movement. This is also how I came across calisthenics. Early on I combined skills from calisthenics with free running as well as many other related sports such as gymnastics, wieghtlifting, handbalancing, climbing, sprinting, crawling and so on.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://ykings.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/001-e1455812997628.jpg" rel="attachment wp-att-1126"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-1126" src="http://ykings.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/001-768x1024.jpg" alt="001" width="615" height="820" /></a>\r\n\r\nMy philosohpy today is simple: "Discovering what my body is capable of, I keep learning new strength patterns, flips, moves and just train and move as much as possible. I am a mover and a life-long learner."\r\n\r\nStart your journey into the world of movement with Ykings and learn the basics. Have the guidance and the progressions I never had and follow and learn from movers like me. Follow me in the app under Dominik_SKY', 'Dominik_SKY: Step into the world of movement', '', 'draft', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'dominik_sky-step-into-the-world-of-movement', '', '', '2016-06-10 14:57:12', '2016-06-10 14:57:12', '', 0, 'http://ykings.com/New/?post_type=post-portfolio&#038;p=1592', 0, 'post-portfolio', '', 0);
